text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild]]%0a%0a!Do not speak Chinese in university lounges%0a%0a:Author: xiranw%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSaid a Duke professor%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn early 2019, an email sent by a Duke professor warning students to not speak Chinese in university lounges sparked widespread outrage. In the email, the professor said that she had been approached by two other faculty members who witnessed students speaking Chinese in lounge/study areas. The two faculty members felt that speaking Chinese in such settings was both impolite and showed the students’ lack of effort to improve their English. They wished to identify those students so that they could “remember them if the students ever interviewed for an internship or asked to work with them for a master’s project”.%0a%0aDenying students academic and professional opportunities simply because and only because they choose to speak in a specific language is a textbook example of linguistic discrimination. And unfortunately, such incidents are not isolated. Speakers of minority languages are often decried as unprofessional and/or incompetent by speakers of the prestigious majority language, despite how the language one speaks in has nothing to do with competence. In a country like the United States with a large immigrant population, such clashes between immigrant languages and English are especially common.%0a%0aSources: https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/28/health/duke-professor-warns-chinese-students-speak-english-trnd/index.html%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 210505-035817-557710#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Discrimination against Spanish speakers in public places %0a-> - rajeev_g%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aI was reminded of a similar incident that took place a couple years ago in New York City, where the language in question was Spanish. There was an American English-speaking white lawyer in line at a store who became very upset that the Spanish-speaking employees were speaking in Spanish to the Spanish-speaking customers. He proceeded to berate the manager for the conduct of his employees and threaten to call ICE on the employees. While it's problematic enough that he believed that speaking a language that both speakers agree to use is offensive to him somehow, the idea that all Spanish-speaking Americans are undocumented perpetrates linguistic stereotypes. In addition, the idea that one's cultural identity could be weaponized as a tool to challenge one's legal status is reflective of a system that sees diversity of language and culture not as a strength, but as something to be eliminated.%0a%0aSource: https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/5/16/17362712/white-man-lawyer-threatens-spanish-speaking-workers-new-york-aaron-schlossberg%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210505-035817-557710#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a#foxbegin 210501-060625-504340#%0a(:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a[-30.04.2021 - 23:06-] &nbsp; %0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c%0a{[foxdelrange button 210501-060625-504340 {$FullName} ]}%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1end:)%0a!!!!!Abi_S%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0a'''Banning language?'''%0a>>messageitem%3c%3c%0aI'm not sure why the professors thought that only English could be spoken on campus. I know I've heard the argument from people with similar perspectives is that they should be able to hear the conversation and understand it, in which case, pick up Chinese?  %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210501-060625-504340#%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: B:)%0a(:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)
